io.undertow.util

Class PathMatcher<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.undertow.util.PathMatcher<T>

  • public class PathMatcher<T>
extends Object
    Handler that dispatches to a given handler based of a prefix match of the path.

    This only matches a single level of a request, e.g if you have a request that takes the form:

    /foo/bar

    Author:
    Stuart Douglas

      • addPrefixPath

        public PathMatcher addPrefixPath(String path,
                                 T handler)
        Adds a path prefix and a handler for that path. If the path does not start with a / then one will be prepended.

        The match is done on a prefix bases, so registering /foo will also match /bar. Exact path matches are taken into account first.

        If / is specified as the path then it will replace the default handler.

        Parameters:
        path - The path
        handler - The handler
